import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='miles', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['miles'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['miles'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['miles'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['miles'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of miles driven?')
    plt.xlabel('Miles')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='gas', data=data)
    plt.title('How has the gas consumption changed over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Gas Consumption')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna()
    sns.scatterplot(x='miles', y='gas_per_mile', data=data)
    plt.axhline(y=data['gas_per_mile'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Average gas consumption per mile: {:.2f}'.format(data['gas_per_mile'].mean()))
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.title('What is the average gas consumption per mile?')
    plt.xlabel('Miles')
    plt.ylabel('Gas consumption per mile')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
